erSets</a> → <a href=\"./Lean/Linter/Init.html#Lean.Linter.LinterOptions\">Lean.Linter.LinterOptions</a></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Lean/Linter/Init.html#Lean.Linter.LinterOptions.mk","kind":"ctor","line":73,"name":"Lean.Linter.LinterOptions.mk","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Linter/Init.lean#L73-L83"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">structure</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Linter/Init.html#Lean.Linter.LinterOptions\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Linter</span>.<span class=\"name\">LinterOptions</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The `LinterOptions` structure is used to determine whether given linters are enabled.\n\nThis structure contains all the data required to do so, the `Options` set on the command line\nor by the `set_option` command, and the `LinterSets` that have been declared.\n\nA single structure holding this data is useful since we want `getLinterValue` to be a pure\nfunction: determining the `LinterSets` would otherwise require a `MonadEnv` instance.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Linter/Init.html#Lean.Linter.LinterOptions","kind":"structure","line":73,"name":"Lean.Linter.LinterOptions","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Linter/Init.lean#L73-L83"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">opaque</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Linter/Init.html#Lean.Linter.linterSetsExt\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Linter</span>.<span class=\"name\">linterSetsExt</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Environment.html#Lean.Persistent